condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :4.01 | Description :The Borrower, through MoTC, has adopted the GAC Action Plan, satisfactory to the Bank. | DueDate :30-Dec-2009

Finance Agreement :4.01 | Description :The MoTC has entered into an agreement, in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank, withthe PMC for the purposes of carrying out activities under the Project | Due Date :30-Dec-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section I | Description :the Borrower shall ensure that the PMC is maintained with a composition,resources and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :18-Mar-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section I | Description :The Borrower shall prepare RAPs and implement EMPs | Due Date :11-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section I | Description :The Borrower shall take necessary measures to facilitate an independentprocurement audit and act upon the findings and recommendations of the audit. | Due Date :30-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section II B | Description :The Borrower shall have its Financial Statements audited in accordancewith the provisions of Section 5.09 (b) of the General Conditions | Due Date :30-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section II B | Description :The Borrower shall maintain or cause to be maintained a financialmanagement system in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.09 of the General Conditions | Due Date :30-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section II B | Description :The Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank not later than fortyfive (45) days after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports | Due Date :30-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section II | Description :Not later than December 31, 2010, and annually thereafter, the Borrower,through the MoTC, shall carry out jointly with the Bank, annual reviews of the progress made in carrying out the Project |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 section II | Description :Preparation of Project Reports in accordance with Section 5.08 of theGeneral Conditions and on the basis of indicators agreed withthe Bank. | Due Date :11-Jun-2010

title.narrative: Reduce, by the end of the Project, the rate (per 100 million veh-km) of road crash fatalities along the Project road sections by atleast 10%
Works, Goods, and Consulting Services contracts processed and managed by the PMC
Training received by the Committee staff from PMC (staff-hours)
Number of kilometers of roads upgraded (cumulative km)
Updating of road data for Republican roads (% of total length per year)
Reduce, by the end of the Project, Road User Costs from US$0.26/veh-km to US$0.23/veh-km on Project road sections.
Proportion of the Republican road network length that are in Good or Fair conditions
Implementation and Effective use of Road Management System by the Committee

actual.value: RAMS activities framework completed. Equipment tested. The system was rolled out in 14 oblasts. However, additional 7 monthsservice agreement was signed in Dec. 2019 for capacity building and to complete some elements of the system.

title.narrative: Prepare road safety strategy and action plan
Road asset management strategy, Rolling multiyearroad maintenance, and rehabilitation programestablished

actual.value: system in place, tested, rolled out in 14 oblasts.
